svcsubproc.para:
With the system completely discharged, both knobs are out (
                Figure 41
                ).

When system pressure reaches 65 psi, the red knob (trailer supply) may be pushed in (
                Figure 42
                ) and should stay in, charging the trailer system and releasing the trailer brakes. The yellow knob
                (system park) may now be pushed in (
                Figure 43
                ) which will supply air to the tractor spring brakes, releasing them.
